snippet.textDisplay: Those who are correcting people that it is a Hamd and not a song should know that it is neither completely a Hamd nor part of worship but as it is, a devotional song of the Qawwali genre that incorporates Hamd and conveys the spiritual message of Islam through the words of a worshiper/devotee. It is Sufi music but *calling it a song is perfectly fine and not against any religious doctrine.*

snippet.textDisplay:
Well, most of the songs which has the sufiana flavours in Coke studio have been full of lyrics with wrong and sinful interpretation. But this one is perfect in every bits. I want to thank the genius composer Haider saab, the singers and the musicians and the STRINGS for making this song happen. 
Love from Bangladesh
P.S. (Above mentioned comment is totally my own observation. It is not meant to hurt others' choice or taste or faith in terms of lyrics.)
